<p>The Department of Computer Applications at Ilahia College of Engineering and Technology (ICET), Muvattupuzha, offers a two-year full-time MCA programme with an intake of 60 students. Established in 2008, the department aims to produce dynamic IT professionals equipped with strong technical, communication, and leadership skills, while also emphasizing ethics and social responsibility. The department is headed by Dr. Sulfath P. M. along with experienced faculty and staff members. It provides excellent infrastructure including a well-equipped MCA lab, smart classrooms, and a department library in addition to the central library. To enhance learning, students are exposed to seminars, workshops, industrial visits, and training sessions in communication, aptitude, and reasoning through the placement cell. Many graduates have secured placements in reputed companies like Wipro, IBS, Speridian, and ClaySys. The department encourages lifelong learning, innovation, and industry-ready skills, with a strong focus on both academic performance and extracurricular achievements</p>
